			<ns0:name>cbiffle@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/cbiffle@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">This is actually deliberate, though the wording is awkward.  We were concerned that about:flags is persistent, and people might accidentally leave Native Client enabled forever.  While we're not aware of any security vulnerabilities, we're professional paranoids and we're playing it safe.  For Arctic, we would like this info bar to remain visible.

As for the wording...this is partially a side effect of the mechanism we used to enable the infobar.  The command-line flag and the about:flags toggle are essentially the same thing.  This is the same wording/mechanism used for the flag to disable the sandbox, for example.

Passing to Christian to either close or correct me as needed.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-02-14T22:17:17.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-02-14T22:17:17.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates>
